<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1437,690,1942]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1845,1870]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin adjective “ 
<emphasis box="[660,775,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">triangulus</emphasis>
”, meaning three-cornered, or triangular, referring to the pointed rather than notched anterior angle of the ocellar triangle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
